The office also includes a kindergarten, the architects understood.
The administrative building Avriopoint in Brno is the new headquarters of Arch.Design.
No one would expect that it also hides a miniature ball with everything that belongs to it - with colorful walls, imaginative furniture, a bunch of toys and even a miniature playground on the outdoor terrace.
Since October last year, it has been open to the children of Arch.Design employees.
Design and architectural company Arch.Design, from whose studios came a number of important buildings in Brno, counted with space for its company mini-stool from the first drawings of the Avriopoint building.
It employs nearly 90 people, mostly at the age of the baby boom, and she cared so that women designers and architects could quickly return to work.
Along with the possibility of shorter jobs, the kindergarten is a benefit that Arch.Design offers to its employees as part of the social program.
Builders and architects have the opportunity to combine demanding jobs with caring for a child.
The mini-school was invented by Arch.Design employees and with the support of the management, they managed to obtain a grant from the European Union and the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs.
The mini-school is financed by the European Social Fund through the Operational Programme Human Resources and Employment and the State Budget of the Czech Republic.
Thanks to grant funding (subsidy of CZK 2.8 million) they were able to purchase equipment and equipment and for two years to provide qualified personnel and operations.
