In this way, parents make more productive use of their working hours.
It is not surprising that a naturally loyal employee-employee relationship is created here.
Arch.Design has thus been included among Czech companies, which offer a significant benefit in recruiting new employees, are family-friendly and through this program has strengthened personnel marketing.
The House of Bones fascinates even after 100 years. Look into the interiors of Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>
The roof looks like the back of a prehistoric lizard, the staircase resembles the back of a dinosaur, and the balconies are open fish mouth.
This is the Casa Batll<0xC3><0xB3> in Barcelona by the Catalan architect Antoni Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>.
Due to its organic shapes, it earned the nickname House of Bones from the locals.
Organic shapes, wild colors, unusual use of stone, fragments of tiles and mosaics, a fa<0xC3><0xA7>ade reminiscent of scales and ubiquitous soft curves, all this is typical of Antoni Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>’s Art Nouveau style.
The facade of the house is played out by dream lines, delicate colors and textures reminiscent of nature and animals.
When you observe in detail, you can see geometry, rhythm and a precisely thought-out order.
At night, the whole facade of the house sounds even more dramatic, it is illuminated so that the impression of the brightness of the colors is further enhanced.
The twisting and twisting of shapes is equally apparent in interiors.
The wood in the waves copies the window frames, railings, decorative elements of the doors, cockatoos and bars.
The Batll<0xC3><0xB3> House, located in the Eixample district on the bustling Passeig de Gr<0xC3><0xA0>cia No. 43 shopping street, was built in 1877 by architect Emilio Sala Cortes.
Reconstruction took two years and the house was completed in 1906.
The investor, the wealthy industrialist Josep Batll<0xC3><0xB3>, originally insisted on demolishing the old building and building a completely new one, but soon accepted Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>'s idea of an unusual and cheaper reconstruction.
The Casa Batll<0xC3><0xB3>, however, was not designed by Antoni Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> himself.
It was designed by the architect Josep Maria Jujol.
It was on his design board that decorations for the representative apartment of the owner of the property and the use of mosaics on the facade were created.
A number of other artists and artists also worked on the fa<0xC3><0xA7>ade.
The joint work on the Casa Batll<0xC3><0xB3> project started Jujol’s successful collaboration with Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>.
Jujol was involved in the construction of Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>'s Casa Mil<0xC3><0xA1> and the Park Güell, in which there are other works of Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>.
From the locals, the house soon after its completion, thanks to its organic shapes, earned the nickname "House of Bones".
Others, due to the specific mechanism of opening the windows, began to call it a "swinging house".
It is also said that on the top of the building is depicted the sword of Saint George, patron saint of Catalonia.
Hidden religious motifs also contain other sculptural elements of the building.
Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> designed a unique central heating system with ventilation vents and typical chimneys for his time.
Bizarre may seem their forty-five degree inclination.
When Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> was created, he absolutely did not respect the building regulations of the time and did not allow himself to be bound by them.
At the beginning of the construction, he obtained a building permit from the city, but the data on the planned reconstruction were so vague that two years later, when completed, the city council was devastated and requested a correction.
For example, councillors were troubled by the fact that the building also interfered with the pillars of the public sidewalk.
It was never corrected, on the contrary: only fifteen days after the challenge of the city part, Josep Batll<0xC3><0xB3> requested (and successfully obtained) permission to rent the two highest floors of the building.
The owner himself moved to the lower floors.
In the gallery on the second floor there was a social lounge and on the third floor a bedroom and a private part of the apartment.
The ground floor was rented jewelry.
The entire six-storey house crosses the stairs, which can be climbed up to the roof terrace itself.
The essential elements of the reconstruction were the abolition of all right angles and straight lines and their replacement with curved walls.
Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> also worked with a modern concept of interconnecting spaces.
The social part can be fully connected by opening the salon doors and the larger company can communicate comfortably together without maintaining the privacy necessary for more intimate conversations.
In addition to the new fa<0xC3><0xA7>ade, the house with Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>’s reconstruction also received an unconventional roof and two additional floors.
Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>’s play with light, blue and white glazed tiles, with which the inner courtyard is covered, and skylights is also impressive.
The game of two colors delivers maximum light on all floors of the house.
It was enough to simply bet on the principle that white reflects light more than dark, which absorbs the sun's rays on the contrary.
The Casa Batll<0xC3><0xB3>, which was listed as a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 2005, can be visited by anyone.
On the first floor of the house is the most spacious and honorable apartment available to the public.
The owners decided to take this step only in 2002, on the occasion of the celebration of the 150th anniversary of the birth of the famous creator.
They stayed at the tours because they found it to be a very profitable business and in addition, they expanded the tours with common and attic spaces, including a roof terrace.
Entrance to the monument is definitely not negligible, it is 16.50 euros and students, pensioners, groups and holders of tourist cards have a 20% discount.
The sum far exceeds the price of admission to other Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> buildings in the city.
If you want to taste the true atmosphere of a house with dragon towers, you need to quickly socialize with some of the inhabitants of the mansion and visit it directly at home.
How to choose a mattress and a grill: women have different requirements than men
Not a superb bed frame, but the quality of the lying area, i.e. mattresses and grill, give the basis of a really good bed.
However, they need to be complemented harmoniously to suit a particular user.
When choosing, a lot of things are decided, from weight, height, age, health status and the gender of the owner.
It is also important the type of interior into which the mattress and the grill are made.
Typical example?
For example, on weekend cottages, where they do not regularly sink, latex mattresses are not suitable, because they are slower to "heat up".
In addition, they have a significantly higher weight than standard polyurethane mattresses.
Sometimes it is necessary to turn them regularly.
If they don’t have a lot of air ducts in the core, and they’re still on a hard board, they retain moisture: mold could also appear underneath them.
The choice also depends on the habit.
Those who have spent a long time abroad, where very high mattresses with a softening layer are often used, will hardly feel good on a low and hard surface.
"Maybe all the hockey players who came back from the NHL complained to me that they weren't sleeping here."
"They needed mattresses with a softening layer of lazy foam on their slashed shoulders, heels, and hips."
"These are also recommended for people with diabetes who have a nervous system disorder, so they misreceive "information" from joints and skin," explains Sylva Hadamczik, who specializes in upholstered furniture.
Therefore, many hockey players, but also other customers, years ago, mattresses with lazy foam were looking for.
"Today it is alright, suitable mattress has Tempur, Italian Magniflex, but also Czech Tropico."
You don't have to be an NHL fighter to appreciate lazy foam.
This "miracle" works simply.
It optimizes its rigidity and shape according to the absorbed heat or adapts to your warm body.
Nothing pushes you, at night you will not turn over like after a hard game.
You'll just get a better night's sleep.
Linen foam also acts as a protection against bedbugs.
When choosing the size of the mattress, add the length of the foot to your height, which is about 21 to 34 cm.
Both a man and a woman with a height of about 180 cm need a bed of 210 to 220 cm.
The minimum width for one should be 90 cm for a double bed, so together 180 cm.
For single beds, for example, singles, it is recommended at least 120 to 140 cm.
For convenience and a possible visit.
"Otherwise, the rule for the width of the bed is simple: when lying on your back, you should have your hands comfortably slightly bent in the elbow," advises Ing. Helena Prokopov<0xC3><0xA1>, a master craftsman of the Department of Upholsterers and Decorators, who is already devoted to the issues of healthy sleep and ergonomics of furniture.
For a double bed, everyone needs their own grill and mattress, but here be careful when buying to adjust the heights of the mattresses.
Otherwise, there will be nothing left but to mount the grids to different heights, but you may not succeed with each frame of the bed.
Foam mattresses should have a height of at least 14 cm, types with a spring skeleton of at least 15, of which at least three centimeters count on the molding and firing layer.
"When you touch your hands or sit on a mattress, you definitely must not feel the springs," warns Helena Prokopov<0xC3><0xA1>.
Each mattress requires a certain type of grid.
Full-coloured beds, where the mattresses and substrate are like mature Siamese twins, have nothing to do in the bedrooms.
Mattresses are poorly ventilated, you can not wash their cover, which is already common today.
And since we usually sweat 0.2 to 0.75 l of sweat per night, it is clear that after five to seven years the mattress will start to resemble a large (and clogged) mesh.
Even therefore, experts reject advertising slogans about the life of mattresses up to 25 years, or even a lifetime warranty.
But everything has its own buts.
Therefore, the advice from the sellers: for mattresses with a width of 120 or 140 cm, do not give up the detachable coating, but add a mattress protector, which you can easily remove and wash.
Even though mattress covers are commonly produced today, they have slipped around the circuit, so that after opening we get two parts (very important for washing and washing size!), nevertheless, manipulation in larger types (and in one person) during the shooting could be reminiscent of a heavyweight fight.
Do you have a hard board in your bed instead of a grid?
Oh, never!
Maximum on the bed intended for visits for one night.
However, still provide the board with ventilation holes (if it does not already have them) and use a mattress with a spring skeleton and a height of at least 15 cm with springs in bags (from it.Taschenfederkern) and a wicking layer.
Polyurethane mattress does not belong on such a substrate.
Latex or sandwich mattresses (e.g. a combination of latex and coconut) will be suitable for non-laying lamella grilles with 14 to 18 lamellas, but you will always pay for grilles with more lamellas, 28 and more, where the lamellas in the lumbar area are doubled and their stiffness can be regulated.
The positioning slat grids do not include mattresses with a spring skeleton, because they do not react to the positioning.
In addition to adjusting the stiffness of the lamella, the so-called shoulder cradle can also be used.
It is a special lamella fastening, which allows you to push or even tilt the lamella so that the shoulder of the sleeper is nicely "bumped".
For men who have "shoulder across the back", definitely an important thing.
Even mattress manufacturers remember it, which in "men's" began to use a softening zone precisely in the shoulder area.
Women also remember - they in turn give them a softer surface in the places of the hips.
For the most demanding customers, wing or plate racks with so-called multitorsion springing are designed.
The pressure is broken down into several points and the tension is reduced.
However, beware, once you apply the right mattress and grill the wrong pillow (big and "punched"), most of the "plus" will disappear.
The basic rule is simple: the pillow is to support the head and the tips only interfere with the shoulders so that the shoulder muscles can relax.
