Interviews, emails and other documents published in October 2009 in the New York Times stated that Mr. Ensign helped Douglas Hampton, one of his assistants, secure a lucrative lobby that was to lead to Mr. Hampton and his wife, Cynthia, being silenced about the senator’s relationship with her.
Mrs. Hampton once worked as a treasurer in the Ensign campaign.
